INSERT INTO "position" VALUES(797,'queensland-michael-healy-cairns','sex_work','Voted YES (Ayes) on the second reading of the Criminal Code (Decriminalising Sex Work) and Other Legislation Amendment Bill 2024, which decriminalised sex work in Queensland. The named division was carried 49–35 on 2 May 2024; Michael Healy is recorded in the Ayes.',1);
INSERT INTO "position" VALUES(798,'queensland-michael-healy-cairns','first_nations','Voted NOE on the second reading of the Brisbane Olympic and Paralympic Games Arrangements and Other Legislation Amendment Bill 2024 (28 November 2024), opposing the omnibus bill that repealed the Path to Treaty Act 2023 (which ended Queensland''s First Nations Treaty Institute and Truth-telling and Healing Inquiry). The bill passed 53 to 35.',1);
INSERT INTO "position" VALUES(799,'queensland-bryson-head-callide','religious_freedom','Voted against the Respect at Work and Other Matters Amendment Bill 2024 on its third reading (10 September 2024). Opposition MPs argued the Bill threatened religious freedom and free speech and did not adequately protect faith-based organisations.',1);
