INSERT INTO "position" VALUES(1096,'queensland-james-lister-southern-downs','integrity','Lister (LNP) said he ''wholeheartedly support[s]'' the Crime and Corruption (Restoring Reporting Powers) Amendment Bill 2025, praising the restoration of CCC public reporting and criticising the former Labor government for spending taxpayer money to conceal CCC reports about Jackie Trad and Peter Carne. He argued release of information should occur ''when it is merited in the public interest'' and commended the bill to the House.',1);
